# Base44 App Rules

## Stack
- React 18 + Vite + Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui (in `src/components/ui/`)
- Lucide React for icons (only import icons you know exist)
- Backend: Deno Deploy functions in `functions/` — each is a standalone HTTP handler
- DB: `base44.entities.*` SDK (no raw SQL, no REST calls to internal DB)
- Auth: `base44.auth.me()` returns current user `{ id, email, full_name, role }`

## File Structure Rules
- New page → `src/pages/MyPage.jsx` + add `<Route>` in `src/App.jsx` manually
- New component → `src/components/domain/ComponentName.jsx` (keep files < 150 lines)
- New backend function → `functions/myFunction.js`
- Entity schemas → `entities/EntityName.json` (always write full schema, no placeholders)

## Backend Function Template
```js
import { createClientFromRequest } from 'npm:@base44/sdk@0.8.25';
Deno.serve(async (req) => {
  const base44 = createClientFromRequest(req);
  const user = await base44.auth.me();
  if (!user) return Response.json({ error: 'Unauthorized' }, { status: 401 });
  // ... logic ...
  return Response.json({ ok: true });
});
```
- No local imports between function files
- Admin-only: check `user.role !== 'admin'` → return 403
- Connector token: `const { accessToken } = await base44.asServiceRole.connectors.getConnection("clickup")`
- Frontend call: `await base44.functions.invoke('functionName', payload)`

## Frontend Rules
- Never construct Tailwind class names dynamically (no template literals for classes)
- Use design tokens: `bg-background`, `text-foreground`, `text-muted-foreground`, etc.
- Entity CRUD: `base44.entities.EntityName.list/filter/create/update/delete/bulkCreate`
- Use `@tanstack/react-query` for data fetching
- Mobile-first, responsive layouts always

## Entities (key fields)
- `MaintenanceTask`: has `clickup_task_id`, `asset_id`, `status`, `priority`, `assigned_to`
- `Asset`: has `clickup_task_id`, `status`, `condition`, `next_maintenance_due`
- `IntegrityAlert`: `alert_type`, `severity`, `escalation_level`, `evidence_hash`
- `WhistleblowerTip`: `tip_id`, `category`, `status`, `related_alert_id`
- `EvidencePackage`: `package_id`, `alert_id`, `manifest_hash`
- `TalentInsight`: `employee_email`, `skills_evidence`, `learning_path`

## Do NOT
- Use `createPageUrl` — use React Router `<Link to="/path">` with literal paths
- Add `id`, `created_date`, `updated_date`, `created_by` to entity schemas (auto-generated)
- Install packages not in the approved list
- Use `try/catch` unless explicitly required
- Import from `deno.land/x` — use `npm:` prefix